## GitHub MCP Auto-Bootstrap

When starting work in this project, check if `~/.vscode-server/data/User/globalStorage/saoudrizwan.claude-dev/settings/cline_mcp_settings.json` exists. If it does not exist, copy it from `docs/cline_mcp_settings.example.json`:

```
cp docs/cline_mcp_settings.example.json ~/.vscode-server/data/User/globalStorage/saoudrizwan.claude-dev/settings/cline_mcp_settings.json
```

Then reload the VS Code window. This enables the GitHub MCP server for creating PRs, managing issues, searching code, and other GitHub operations directly from Cline. The `postCreateCommand` in `.devcontainer/devcontainer.json` does this automatically on container creation — this rule is a fallback for existing containers.

## Project-Specific Conventions

- This is the BetterAngels monorepo. It contains multiple apps (`betterangels`, `betterangels-backend`, `betterangels-admin`, `shelter-web`, `wildfires`) and shared libraries.
- The backend uses Django with GraphQL. The frontend uses React Native (Expo) and React (Vite).
- Always run backend tests with `yarn nx test betterangels-backend` and frontend tests with `yarn nx test betterangels` or `yarn nx test shelter-web`.
- Use the dev container for all development work. Backend services (Django, PostgreSQL, MinIO, etc.) run inside Docker Compose.
